summary: Completed comprehensive frontend testing of TripCost Vanilla JS SPA with modern SaaS design. All 12 required features tested and working perfectly including homepage sections, calculator interactivity, city pages, nomad rankings, destinations, and all new legal pages with proper navigation.
passed_tests: Homepage loads with hero section, trust badges (4), features grid, how it works, and top cities (6 cards)
Calculator page loads with modern design and all interactive dropdowns (city, housing, lifestyle)
Calculator updates correctly when changing selections: Bali $8,885→$2,365→$1,705→$2,860
City page (/city/lisbon) shows hero with image, 4 KPI cards, cost breakdown, and FAQ section
Nomad page shows rankings table with score bars for all 19 cities
Destinations page shows grid of all 19 city cards with scores and costs
About page (/about) loads with mission section and company information
Legal page (/legal) loads with legal notice and disclaimer content
Privacy page (/privacy) loads with comprehensive privacy policy content
Terms page (/terms) loads with complete terms of service content
Navigation works between all pages via header nav links (Home, Destinations, Calculator, Nomad Rankings, About)
Footer shows all legal links (Privacy, Terms, Legal) and company section links working correctly
